Pa<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>

<head>
    <style>
        / simple selector /
        /* div,p{
            background-color: aqua;
        } */

        / combinator /
        /* 1 descendennt   space   all level child*/
        /* div p {
            background-color: aqua;
        } */

        /* 2 child selector    >     only his child,no grand parent relation*/
        /* 
        div>p {
            background-color: aqua;
        }

        section>p {
            background-color: red;
        } */

        /* 3 adjacent sibling selector     +     element outside the relation (means nearest element jst outside)*/
        div+p {
            border: 2px solid rgb(243, 7, 47);
        }
        
        /* div+p {
            background-color: yellow;
        } */

        / tilt /
        /*4  general sibling     ~   (shift + tab above key  `(abactic)  )  all element after parent tag*/
        div~p {
            background-color: yellow;
        }

        
    </style>
</head>

<body>
    <h2>General Sibling Selector</h2>

    <p>The general sibling selector (~) selects all elements that are next siblings of a specified element.</p>

    <p>Paragraph 1.</p>



    <div>
        <p>Paragraph 2.</p>
        <code>
            <p>
                code
            </p>
        </code>
    </div>

